Many of the most promising AI stocks have fallen out of favor recently thanks to economic uncertainty and AI spending concerns.  Advanced Micro Devices (NASDAQ: AMD), which is more commonly referred to simply as AMD, is often overlooked by investors because it holds a distant-second market share in the data center graphics processing units (GPU) space to chipmaking behemoth Nvidia, which has about 95% of the space.
